node.text: The boys and I love doing activities together - especially ones that have to do with food 🥰 TexasWIC.org has so many fun, healthy food ideas and activities to introduce healthy eating habits to your kids. Introducing new healthy foods to my kids is so important–today’s new veggie is celery! Also, if you’ve got picky eaters, check out Texas WIC’s online class for even more help!Visit TexasWIC.org for more nutrition inspiration and tips on how to keep your children healthy in every stage! #sponsored @txwicsouthplains

node.text: It was really cool to interview Dr. Khan about the COVID-19 vaccine. She was a wealth of knowledge! I hope you watch this video to learn more about them! Yay science! #HealthyTexas #ThisIsOurShot

How are you spreading kindness? Show me your acts of kindness and tag @IvorySoap and #IvoryKindness! #IvoryPartner #ad

node.text: Every time I sing this song and listen to the lyrics, I cry. I cry because I’m so grateful for my children and I am so blessed that I get to kiss each of them everyday. I cherish every moment that I’m given with them and this song will forever be a part of our lives. As a kid I remember moms always crying and thinking they were crazy and weird and now I’m that weird and crazy lady times a million. Happy tears. I hope you love this @mamasingmysong keepsake song as much as we do.
